<div class="comment-content">
<p>Hey Mark,<br/>
Try this and let me know if it works:</p>
<p><code>c:\windows\fart.exe "S:\misc_videos\Skate\*.wvx" G:\_Media_Center\ "&lt;Ref href=G:\_Media_Center\</code></p>
<p>Notice the quotation mark before &lt;ref &#8211; also notice that there isn&#8217;t one at the end &#8211; this is because the back slash would escape it.</p>
<p>Hope that helps <img src="//emtunc.org/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;"/></p>
