<p>Love your utility&#8230; I am using it as part of a project to make it easy to migrate certain web apps from one host to our CMS&#8230; </p>
<p>I used it to search/replace several strings in files and filenames without any problems until I tried todo this:</p>
<p>fart -ic *.html &#8220;http://www.domain.org/&#8221; &#8220;/&#8221;</p>
<p>in other words, in all the *.html files I want to replace <a href="http://www.domain.org/" onclick="__gaTracker('send', 'event', 'outbound-comment', 'http://www.domain.org/', 'http://www.domain.org/');" rel="nofollow">http://www.domain.org/</a> with a simple forward slash. I tried this with and without the double quotes and every way I could think&#8230; </p>
<p>Also, after reading this blog, I tried to use the single quote by itself accidentally and so now I did replace <a href="http://www.domain.org/" onclick="__gaTracker('send', 'event', 'outbound-comment', 'http://www.domain.org/', 'http://www.domain.org/');" rel="nofollow">http://www.domain.org/</a> with &#8216;/ (single quote followed by slash)&#8230; and now I can&#8217;t change this back to anything either&#8230; pretty sure this has to do with escaping special characters and such and I don&#8217;t know how with your util&#8230; </p>
<p>Any pointers would be helpful, thanks!<br/>
Patrick Steil</p>
