<p>I want to find:</p>
<p>&lt;code&gt;&lt;a href=&#8221;Site/Map.html&#8221; rel=&#8221;nofollow&#8221;&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</p>
<p>and replace with:</p>
<p>&lt;code&gt;&lt;a href=&#8221;/site/map.html&#8221; rel=&#8221;nofollow&#8221;&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</p>
<p>and for example this gives me errors:</p>
<p>&lt;code&gt;fart -iC <a href="http://www.ntcumc.org" onclick="__gaTracker('send', 'event', 'outbound-comment', 'http://www.ntcumc.org', 'http://www.ntcumc.org');" rel="nofollow">http://www.ntcumc.org</a>\people.html &lt;a href=&#8221;site/map.html&#8221; rel=&#8221;nofollow&#8221;&gt; &lt;a href=&#8221;/site/map.html&#8221; rel=&#8221;nofollow&#8221;&gt;<br/>
&lt; was unexpected at this time.&lt;/code&gt;</p>
<p>I understand this is a command line interpreter issue, have also tried escaping the brackets and double quotes with ^ and got this:</p>
<p>&lt;code&gt;fart -iC <a href="http://www.ntcumc.org" onclick="__gaTracker('send', 'event', 'outbound-comment', 'http://www.ntcumc.org', 'http://www.ntcumc.org');" rel="nofollow">http://www.ntcumc.org</a>\people.html ^&lt;a&gt;^&lt;a&gt;<br/>
