<ol class="children">
<li id="comment-1305" class="comment byuser comment-author-e-mikail-t bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
<article id="div-comment-1305" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='//1.gravatar.com/avatar/ad493516bfdd45a2bd02f872625c64d1?s=56&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/ad493516bfdd45a2bd02f872625c64d1?s=112&amp;d=monsterid&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo' height='56' width='56'/> <b class="fn">E Mikail T</b> <span class="says">says:</span> </div> 
<div class="comment-metadata">
<a href="http://emtunc.org/blog/03/2011/farting-the-easy-way-find-and-replace-text/#comment-1305">
<time datetime="2011-10-17T15:11:08+00:00">
October 17, 2011 at 3:11 PM </time>
</a>
</div> 
</footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>Hello Umesh,<br/>
Have you tried using the -r switch to recursively search through directories? You would put the -r switch followed with the search path &#8220;C:\Users\username\AppData\Roaming\Mozilla\Firefox\Profiles\&#8221;&#8230; that way the script will search all sub-directories of \Profiles.</p>
<p>Hope that helps.</p>
</div> 
